---
import Main from "../layouts/Main.astro";
import Hero from "../components/Hero.astro";
import Cards from "../components/Cards.astro";
import Skills from "../components/Skills.astro";
import Me from "../components/Me.astro";
---

<Main title="Darran O'Shea">
  <section>
    <div class="hero-section">
      <h1 class="text-3xl">Darran O'Shea</h1>
      <div class="paragraphs">
        <p>
          Technical delivery lead at <mark>Jarilo Design</mark>. Self-taught,
          hospitality-raised, still ships code.
        </p>
        <p>
          Currently shipping 350+ projects a year and figuring out what
          AI-augmented delivery actually looks like in practice.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <span>350+</span>
        <span>projects delivered annually</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span>41%</span>
        <span>increase in team output from AI adoption</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span>20%</span>
        <span>reduction in project timelines</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span>90+</span>
        <span>projects shipped as a developer before promotion</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-grid work">
      <h2>Selected Work</h2>

      <div class="section-right">
        <ul>
          <li class="stretched-link">
            <article>
              <div class="row">
                <span class="sage">Delivery</span>
                <h3>
                  <a href="/notes/ai-adoption-rollout"
                    >AI Adoption Rollout at Jarilo</a
                  >
                </h3>
              </div>
              <p>
                How I introduced AI tooling across a team of designers,
                developers, and account managers — and what the numbers looked
                like after.
              </p>
            </article>
          </li>
          <li class="stretched-link">
            <article>
              <div class="row">
                <span class="dustyblue">Product</span>
                <h3>
                  <a href="/notes/ai-adoption-rollout"
                    >Internal Project Management Tool</a
                  >
                </h3>
              </div>
              <p>
                A lightweight internal product built to reduce coordination
                overhead across 350+ concurrent projects.
              </p>
            </article>
          </li>

          <li class="stretched-link">
            <article>
              <div class="row">
                <span class="rosewood">Technical</span>
                <h3>
                  <a href="/notes/ai-adoption-rollout"
                    >Three.js Interactive Experience</a
                  >
                </h3>
              </div>
              <p>
                A client-facing 3D piece built in Three.js and Blender —
                interactive, performant, shipped on deadline.
              </p>
            </article>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-grid">
      <h2>About</h2>

      <div class="section-right">
        <p>
          I spent a decade running bars and restaurants before I taught myself
          to code. I joined Jarilo Design as a web developer in 2022, shipped
          over 90 projects, and was promoted to Technical Operations Lead in
          2024. Now I run delivery across design, development, QA, account
          management, and consultancy.
        </p>
        <p>
          My background is unusual for this role and I think that's the point.
          Managing a kitchen at volume taught me things about coordination and
          calm under pressure that no bootcamp covers. The animation degree
          didn't hurt either — I can get into the detail of a Three.js build or
          a Blender scene without needing a handoff.
        </p>
        <p>
          What I'm most interested in right now is what AI-augmented delivery
          actually looks like when you take it seriously — not the hype, but the
          tooling, the process changes, and the honest accounting of what works
          and what doesn't.
        </p>
        <a href="/about">More about me →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="section-grid notes">
      <h2>Notes</h2>

      <div class="section-right">
        <p>
          A public notebook — thoughts, hacks and lessons, primarily for myself.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <span>AI & Delivery</span>
            <h3>
              What 41% actually means: measuring AI adoption in a real agency
            </h3>
            <p>
              The methodology behind the number, and why output metrics miss
              half the story.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>Process</span>
            <h3>Running 350+ projects a year without losing the thread</h3>
            <p>
              How triage, tempo, and boring systems beat heroics every time.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>Career</span>
            <h3>On coming up through the wrong door</h3>
            <p>
              Hospitality to code to delivery — what the arc looks like from the
              inside.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>Technical</span>
            <h3>Why I still write code as a delivery lead</h3>
            <p>Not a productivity argument — a credibility and empathy one.</p>
          </li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/notes">All notes →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

